Hello,

This email message is a notification to let you know that
a file has been uploaded to the Files area of the neat 
group.

  File        : /Neuro Evolving Virtual Humans.zip 
  Uploaded by : petar_chervenski <petar_chervenski@...> 
  Description : This is an experimental application of HyperNEAT for evolving CTRNN substrates. It's primary target is to examine what are the benefits of using geometry for dynamic control problems. Use "F" to switch between fast and normal mode. Use "C" to switch between CPPN network and substrate views. If you close a window, it will not open anymore. You need Visual Studio 2005 to compile, but it is compatible with other versions, I guess. You have to copy the .H files to your compiler's include directory.  

You can access this file at the URL:
http://groups.yahoo.com/group/neat/files/Neuro%20Evolving%20Virtual%20Humans.zip 

To learn more about file sharing for your group, please visit:
http://help.yahoo.com/help/us/groups/files

Regards,
